line_1: Awe chills my breast, my eyes o'erflow,
line_2: Around my brows no roses glow,

line_1: A band of malcontents with spleen o'erflow;
line_2: ARMS cross'd, brows bent, eyes fix'd, feet marching slow,

line_1: To make the cup of bitterness o'erflow,
line_2: Light on my head, and in my day of woe,

line_1: The rolling Waves their sinking Shells o'erflow,
line_2: And dash them down again to Sands below.

line_1: And gnaws his withered lips, which still o'erflow
line_2: On the damp ground he sits in sullen woe,

line_1: With scraps of antient learning overflow,
line_2: LET the sage DOCTOR (think him one we know)

line_1: 'Tis like a torrent apt to overflow,
line_2: Unless by constant government kept low;

line_1: His Anguish makes my weary'd Eyes o'erflow,
line_2: And loads me with unutterable Woe.

line_1: How tides, when heav'd by pressing moons, o'erflow,
line_2: And sun-born Iris paints her flow'ry bow.

line_1: With kind concern our pitying eyes o'erflow,
line_2: Trace the sad tale, and own another's woe.

line_1: Extreamest Griefs, his suffering Soul o'erflow;
line_2: And every Breath declares incessent Woe;

line_1: Extreamest Griefs, his suffering Soul o'erflow;
line_2: Then he reflects on his malicious Foe.

line_1: Our verdant walks and pleasure-grounds o'erflow.
line_2: With harsh, discordant note, augments our wo;

line_1: Expand each heart, and make each eye o'erflow,
line_2: At these dread scenes of wretchedness and woe.

line_1: Too late his Eyes with gushing Tears o'erflow!
line_2: But oh! too late in Sighs he vents his Woe,

line_1: When rising Floods my Head o'erflow,
line_2: When sinks my Heart in Waves of Woe,
